Quote: <i>Witch Arnoglossus scapha</i> Also called megrim, both names derived from similar European flatfishes. Found only in New Zealand. ... A related but smaller species,  the crested flounder <i>Lophonectes gallus</i>, of northern coastal waters, can be distinguished by a `crest' of long white dorsal fin rays.
